Description:
    Generates a complete audit logging system for tracking changes to sensitive models.
    Automatically tracks User, Account, and Session changes, with optional tracking
    for other models via the Auditable concern.

Features:
    - Automatic change tracking for User, Account, Session models
    - Auditable concern for opt-in tracking on other models
    - Admin-only audit log viewer with search and filters
    - CSV export functionality
    - Automatic cleanup of old logs via SolidQueue
    - Configurable retention period

Example:
    bin/rails generate boilermaker:audit_log
    bin/rails generate boilermaker:audit_log --retention-days=180

    This will create:
        db/migrate/TIMESTAMP_create_audit_logs.rb
        app/models/audit_log.rb
        app/models/concerns/auditable.rb
        app/controllers/admin/audit_logs_controller.rb
        app/views/admin/audit_logs/index.rb
        app/views/admin/audit_logs/show.rb
        app/jobs/audit_log_cleanup_job.rb
        app/controllers/concerns/audit_log_feature.rb
        config/routes/audit_log.rb
        config/recurring.yml (if not exists)
        test/models/audit_log_test.rb
        test/controllers/admin/audit_logs_controller_test.rb

Options:
    --retention-days=N  Number of days to retain audit logs (default: 90)
    --skip-routes       Skip generating route file
    --skip-tests        Skip generating test files
    --skip-config       Skip updating boilermaker.yml
    --skip-seeds        Skip adding seed data (n/a for this generator)

Adding Tracking to Other Models:
    class Document < ApplicationRecord
      include Auditable  # Adds automatic tracking for create/update/destroy
    end

What Gets Logged:
    - Action: create, update, destroy, sign_in, sign_out, impersonation_start, impersonation_end
    - User: Who performed the action
    - Changes: Before/after values (sensitive fields filtered)
    - IP Address and User Agent
    - Metadata: Additional context

Viewing Logs:
    Logs are accessible at /admin/audit_logs (admin only)
    - Filter by model type, action, date range
    - Export to CSV for reporting
    - View detailed change history per record

Cleanup:
    Old logs are automatically deleted based on retention period.
    The cleanup job runs daily at 3am via SolidQueue recurring jobs.

    Manual cleanup:
      AuditLog.cleanup_old_records!
      # or
      AuditLogCleanupJob.perform_now
